# Environment Variables Example

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your actual API key.

```bash
# Required: Your StepFun API key
# Get yours at https://platform.stepfun.ai/
STEPFUN_API_KEY=your_key_here

# Optional: Override API base URL (default: https://api.stepfun.ai/step_plan/v1)
# Note: the files endpoint always uses /v1 regardless of this setting.
# STEPFUN_API_BASE=https://api.stepfun.ai/step_plan/v1

# Optional: Output directory for generated files (default: ~/.zeroclaw/workspace/output)
# OUTPUT_DIR=~/my-output-dir
```

## Notes

- `STEPFUN_API_KEY` is required for all scripts
- Never commit `.env` to version control (it's in `.gitignore`)
- Use `STEPFUN_API_BASE` to override the default API endpoint if needed
- `OUTPUT_DIR` can be any writable directory path
